sentences: Alexa Still (born 1962) is a New Zealand-born flutist based in Oberlin, Ohio, where she is an Associate Professor of Flute at the Oberlin Conservatory of Music.
Still returned to New Zealand for eleven years to take the position of Principal Flute with the New Zealand Symphony Orchestra.
In 1996, Still received a Fulbright Award.
From 2006 to 2007, she was Chair of the Board of Directors for the National Flute Association (USA).
Still has also served on faculty at the University of Colorado at Boulder (1998–2006) and the Sydney Conservatorium of Music (2006–2011).
